40|$|AbstractThe {{isometry}} classification problem {{occupies a}} central role in the theory of quadratic and <b>hermitian</b> <b>forms.</b> This article is a survey of results on the problem for quadratic and <b>hermitian</b> <b>forms</b> over a field and also for <b>hermitian</b> and skew-hermitian <b>forms</b> over a noncommutative division algebra with involution. Rather than adopting a very abstract approach, the problems are stated in matrix or linear-algebraic terms. The known solutions depend crucially on the particular field considered, although there are some general results which are mentioned. While many of the results date back a long time, some recent results, especially those on skew-hermitian forms over a quaternion algebra over a number field, are included...|$|R
40|$|Bilinear {{forms in}} complex normal {{variables}} when matrices {{of the forms}} are rectangular are considered. Expressions for the cumulants, joint cumulants of arbitrary order of hermitian bilinear and <b>hermitian</b> quadratic <b>forms</b> are given. Necessary and sufficient conditions for the independence of two <b>hermitian</b> bilinear <b>forms</b> and a <b>hermitian</b> bilinear and a <b>hermitian</b> quadratic <b>form</b> are stated...|$|R
40|$|We {{present an}} {{adaptation}} of Voronoi theory for imaginary quadratic number fields of class number greater than 1. This includes a characterisation of extreme <b>Hermitian</b> <b>forms</b> which {{is analogous to the}} classic characterisation of extreme quadratic forms as well as a version of Voronoi's famous algorithm which may be used to enumerate all perfect <b>Hermitian</b> <b>forms</b> for a given imaginary quadratic number field in dimensions 2 and 3. We also present an application of the algorithm which allows to determine generators of the general linear group of an Ø_K-lattice...|$|R
